      "id": "handnote",
      "html": " <p>Neat and regular square letters. Phi and omicron are rhomboid in form; standard four-bar sigma; epsilon has horizontal bars of equal length; alpha has a slightly extended apex; mu has extended apices, and all four strokes are full length and off-vertical. There is one instance of ligature in line 3, and interpuncts are in the form of simple triangular incisions.</p> Line 1-4  15-20  Not measured    "
